                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/906: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Prendergast</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-24T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 24, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. In a lengthy official manifesto just published in afternoon press President
                    Busch announces his assumption of complete power in the State and promises a
                    government of “energy and discipline.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Prendergast</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
